# Native styling (Uniwind)

## Default: Uniwind `className`, not custom styles

- Style React Native views with **Uniwind/Tailwind `className`** utilities.
- Do **not** add `StyleSheet.create`, inline `style={{ ... }}`, or hardcoded hex/`rgb()`/`oklch()` in components unless there is no token or utility equivalent.
- Prefer **HeroUI Native** primitives (`Surface`, `Button`, `Card`, etc.) and extend via `className` ÔÇö do not fork component internals.

## Use shared design tokens

Color and spacing must come from the theme defined in `apps/native/global.css`, which mirrors the shared palette in `packages/ui/src/styles/globals.css` (used by web and admin).

**Prefer semantic tokens:**

- `bg-background`, `text-foreground`
- `bg-primary`, `text-primary-foreground`
- `bg-secondary`, `text-secondary-foreground`
- `text-muted-foreground`, `border-border`, `bg-destructive`

**Avoid:**

```tsx
// ÔØî BAD ÔÇö one-off colors
<View style={{ backgroundColor: "#008080" }} />
<Text className="text-[#1a1a1a]" />

// Ô£à GOOD ÔÇö theme tokens
<View className="bg-primary" />
<Text className="text-foreground" />
```

## Adding or changing tokens

1. Update **shared** values in `packages/ui/src/styles/globals.css` when the color is used across web + native.
2. Map the same values in `apps/native/global.css` under `@variant light` / `@variant dark` as `--color-*` (Uniwind syntax).
3. Do not introduce native-only colors in TSX; add them to CSS first, then use `bg-*` / `text-*` classes.

## Theme switching

Use `Uniwind.setTheme("light" | "dark")` via `AppThemeProvider` ÔÇö do not hand-roll dark-mode color overrides in components.

## Exceptions (rare)

- Third-party components that only accept `style` props: pass theme values via `useThemeColor` from `heroui-native` when a `className` is not supported.
- Dynamic values (e.g. animated transforms): `style` is fine for the dynamic part only; keep colors/spacing in `className`.
